value.title: Biden looks for air-clearing in first meeting with Israel's new leader
value.excerpt: When Israel's prime minister visits the White House on Thursday, for the first time in 12 years, it will be someone other than Benjamin Netanyahu.

value.title: Joe Biden taps Milwaukee Mayor Tom Barrett as Luxembourg ambassador
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden has nominated Milwaukee Mayor Tom Barrett to serve as the next U.S. ambassador to Luxembourg. The White House announced the appointment Wednesday. Barrett still needs Senate confirmation to serve,

value.title: Beto O'Rourke pushes Joe Biden to help pass federal voting bill
value.excerpt: Former Congressman Beto O’Rourke is using his political platform to turn up the heat on President Joe Biden on voting rights legislation that is unlikely to pass the U.S. Senate, laying the fate of the legislation squarely at Biden’s feet.

value.title: Biden ally claims Trump greater 'threat' to US than al Qaeda
value.excerpt: A Democratic insider and vocal ally of President Biden claimed last week that former President Trump and his “Trumpist” supporters are a bigger threat to the United States than the Taliban and al Qaeda fighters.

value.title: Climate measures in reconciliation, infrastructure bills will mostly meet Biden's emissions goals, Schumer says
value.excerpt: An analysis from Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer's office estimates that combined, the bipartisan infrastructure bill and $3.5 trillion budget reconciliation bill can meet the majority of President Joe Biden's target to drastically slash emissions by the end of the decade.

value.title: Apple joins lawsuit regarding Trump-era tariffs on Chinese products
value.excerpt: Apple, Intel and Pfizer have joined 3,700 other U.S. businesses in their suit against the U.S. regarding Trump-era tariffs on $300 billion worth of Chinese products, reports Jurist. This lawsuit was first brought by HMTX Industries in September 2020 and initially targeted List 3 tariffs.

value.title: Charles Barkley Blasts Crowd 'Stupidity' For Booing Donald Trump Over Vaccines
value.excerpt: The NBA legend is headlining an event in Alabama on Saturday to encourage people to take the COVID-19 vaccine.

value.title: A top Pennsylvania Republican reboots 'audit' of 2020 vote, removes Trump ally as chair
value.excerpt: A dispute spilled into public view late last week as some Pennsylvania Republicans seek to further investigate the November election.

value.title: With Biden poll numbers plunging, Democrats worry Afghan exit may impact next year's elections
value.excerpt: The rushed U.S. evacuation in Afghanistan appears to be a key contributing factor in the plunge in President Biden's approval rating in new polls. Some Democrats are worried the political fallout could impair their prospects in the 2022 midterms.

value.title: Joe Biden FORGETS Megan Rapinoe's name, slammed for calling her 'America's best'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden's recent praise for Megan Rapinoe accompanied an awkward fumbling as the president forgot her last name

value.title: Israeli Leader Naftali Bennett to Meet with Joe Biden as Mideast Tensions Grow
value.excerpt: The Israeli leader's meeting with President Joe Biden comes amid heightened tensions with regional arch-enemy Iran

value.title: Trump claims Biden's Afghanistan evacuation could be bringing 'terrorists' to America
value.excerpt: In an August 25 statement, Trump asked people to imagine "how many terrorists" were "airlifted out of Afghanistan" and into neighborhoods worldwide.

value.title: Supreme Court rules Biden may not suspend Trump-era 'remain in Mexico' policy for migrants
value.excerpt: A lower federal court said Biden officials improperly halted the Trump-era 'remain in Mexico' policy, which was intended to reduce immigration.

value.title: With cases in Florida surging, DeSantis and Biden square off over coronavirus response
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden and Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis have found their chosen rhetorical rivals in the fight against the coronavirus: each other. And neither seems eager to back down anytime soon.

value.title: Pence slams Biden’s troop withdrawal as ‘foreign policy humiliation’
value.excerpt: In an interview on The Brian Kilmeade Show, Pence recalled Biden’s decision to fully withdraw by Sept. 11, saying that decision set the “disaster in motion.”

value.title: Jack Nicklaus on his Donald Trump endorsement, Tiger’s future — and a pickleball injury
value.excerpt: Legendary golfer, whose travels have been limited by the pandemic, expounds on recent topics at a charity stop in Virginia.

value.title: Column: Donald Trump can’t cram his ‘fake news’ genie back in his bottle
value.excerpt: As Donald Trump may be discovering, once you’ve let that “fake news” genie out of the bottle, it’s impossible to reverse all of the damage it can bring.

value.title: Former Trump adviser: Biden needs to fire top Taliban negotiator Khalilzad
value.excerpt: Lt. Gen. H.R. McMaster, Donald Trump’s former national security adviser, is laying some of the blame for the current chaos in Afghanistan squarely at the feet of Ambassador Zalmay Khalilzad, the Afghan-American diplomat who has been the point man for talks with the Taliban in both Republican and Democratic administrations.

value.title: Lightning-rod Trump supporter Scott Presler's rally canceled in Wilton
value.excerpt: Scott Presler, a political operative identified as a former top strategist for an anti-Muslim group, canceled an appearance Wednesday at Gavin Park that was touted by U.S. Rep. Elise Stefanik and the local Republican Party.

value.title: Sasse urges Biden to tell Taliban 'we're getting our people out however long it takes': 'Damn the deadline'
value.excerpt: In a blistering statement, Sen. Ben Sasse said Biden should be calling the shots, not the Taliban, who said there would be "no extensions" of the deadline set for withdrawal.

value.title: Kamala Harris’ Vietnam Visit Reportedly Held Up By ‘Havana Syndrome’ Scare
value.excerpt: Two or more U.S. staff in Hanoi were evacuated this weekend after feeling symptoms associated with a syndrome experienced by American officials overseas.

value.title: SCOTUS gave Trump leeway on executive actions. Biden wants the same treatment
value.excerpt: The Biden administration faces two major confrontations with the Supreme Court this week, as the justices weigh requests related to the Covid moratorium on evictions and the termination of a Trump practice that forced migrants seeking US asylum to stay in Mexico until their claims could be heard.

value.title: Possible Havana syndrome incident delayed Harris flight to Vietnam
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris' departure for Vietnam was delayed by several hours Tuesday afternoon after her office was informed by the US embassy in Hanoi, Vietnam, of a "report of a recent possible anomalous health incident."

value.title: Kamala Harris calls Biden's Afghanistan decision 'courageous' as others in White House blame Trump
value.excerpt: Vice President Kamala Harris gave credit to President Biden for deciding to end the war in Afghanistan, even though members of the administration – including Biden himself – have blamed former President Trump for agreeing to withdraw U.S. troops.

value.title: Biden to be briefed on intelligence community COVID origin review as early as Tuesday
value.excerpt: President Biden is expected to receive a briefing on the origin of COVID-19 from the intelligence community as early as Tuesday.
